## Limitations

The report is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the inherent biases in sources that may reflect particular ethical or cultural perspectives. Additionally, the legal status and ethical acceptance of euthanasia vary significantly across different jurisdictions, which may affect the generalizability of the findings. Further research could explore more diverse viewpoints and recent developments in euthanasia legislation and ethical discourse.

